section.para:
The List action of the account entity displays paginated set of the existing accounts from the Atomia Automation server. The number of accounts and the page number can be set using the find_options optional argument (by default set to first 100 accounts):atomia.py account list --find_options "{\"result_count\" : \"3\", \"result_page\":\"0\" }"which results with:[
    {
        "current_request_id": "",
        "provisioning_description": "ProvisioningDescription",
        "account_id": "100000",
        "is_active": "true",
        "account_description": "",
        "account_properties": []
    },
    {
        "current_request_id": "",
        "provisioning_description": "ProvisioningDescription",
        "account_id": "100001",
        "is_active": "true",
        "account_description": "",
        "account_properties": [
            {
                "key": "ResellerRootPath",
                "value": "/00/100000/"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "current_request_id": "",
        "provisioning_description": "ProvisioningDescription",
        "account_id": "100002",
        "is_active": "true",
        "account_description": "",
        "account_properties": [
            {
                "key": "ResellerRootPath",
                "value": "/00/100000/"
            }
        ]
    }
]

The Show action of the account entity displays the properties of the account defined by account_number argument (which is required here):atomia.py account show --account_number "100001"which results with:{
    "current_request_id": "",
    "provisioning_description": "ProvisioningDescription",
    "account_id": "100001",
    "is_active": "true",
    "account_description": "",
    "account_properties": [
        {
            "value": "/00/100000/",
            "key": "ResellerRootPath"
        }
    ]
}

The Add action of the account entity creates a new account in the Atomia Automation server, based on the account argument (which is required here):atomia.py account add  --account " { \"account_id\" : \"atomia001\", \"account_properties\" : { \"ResellerRootPath\" : \"/00/100000/\", \"test\":\"myprop\" }, \"account_description\" : \"My desc\", \"provisioning_description\":\"ProvisioningDescription\" }"which results with:{
    "current_request_id": "",
    "provisioning_description": "ProvisioningDescription",
    "account_id": "atomia001",
    "is_active": "false",
    "account_description": "My desc",
    "account_properties": [
        {
            "value": "myprop",
            "key": "test"
        },
        {
            "value": "/00/100000/",
            "key": "ResellerRootPath"
        }
    ]
}
